parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ignition switch can cause electrical fires, stalling, and failure to start, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or death.
Failure of the TFI ignition module can cause stalling, failure to start, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or death.
symptoms: inability to start for 1.5 to 2 hours after stalling
replacement of TFI ignition module multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the alternator can cause electrical fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or death.
symptoms: Black smoke coming from under the hood

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden radiator failure and coolant leaks can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even fires, which can result in accidents or injuries.
Leaking engine valve cover gaskets can cause fuel odors, engine compartment fires, and engine damage, leading to accidents or injuries.

Fuel system leaks can cause fires, which can lead to serious accidents, injuries, and fatalities. Leaks can also release combustible gasoline vapors into the passenger compartment, posing a significant risk to occupants.
symptoms: Strong gasoline odor inside the vehicle
fuel expelled from breached rubber hoses or quick connect fittings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective "O"-rings in the fuel rail can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Breached Rubber Hoses or Quick Connect Fittings
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Breached rubber hoses or quick connect fittings can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: combustible gasoline expelled into the engine compartment.
